    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Sector Rotation",
      "explanation_en": "Sector rotation is when investors shift capital from one industry group to another based on changing economic conditions or momentum signals. Even on flat market days like today, individual sectors can show strong momentum \u2014 uranium and nuclear energy stocks scored 95 while the broad market barely moved. Identifying these rotations early is one of the primary ways active managers aim to outperform a passive index like VOO.",
